auguratus] Cicero was elected augur in the summer of 53 to fill the vacancy caused by the death of P. Crassus (not M. Crassus as HM. say, cp. Plut. Crass. 36) in the Parthian war. By the Domitian law of 104 (Ρ) B.C.‚ which had been re·enacted in 63 after its abrogation by Sulla in 81, the election of augur rested with-a minority of the tribes (17 out of 35 chosen by lot).
